

Write a program that, for a given two numbers N and x, calculates the sum S = 1 + 1!/x + 2!/x2 + â€¦ + N!/xN.

    Use only one loop. Print the result with 5 digits after the decimal point.
    
let N = +gets();
let x = +gets();
const fact = (m) => {
    if (m == 0 || m == 1) {
        return 1;
    }
    return m * fact(m - 1);
}
let S = 1;
for (let i = 1; i <= N; i += 1) {
    S += fact(i) / (x ** i);
}
print(S.toFixed(5))
